74      public boolean contains(Charset cs) {
75          return ((cs.name().equals("US-ASCII"))
76                  || (cs.name().equals("GBK"))
77                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-1"))
78                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-2"))
79                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-3"))
80                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-4"))
81                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-5"))
82                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-6"))
83                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-7"))
84                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-8"))
85                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-9"))
86                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-13"))
87                  || (cs.name().equals("UTF-8"))
88                  || (cs.name().equals("UTF-16"))
89                  || (cs.name().equals("UTF-16LE"))
90                  || (cs.name().equals("UTF-16BE"))
91                  || (cs.name().equals("ISO-8859-15"))
92                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1251"))
93                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1252"))
94                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1253"))
95                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1254"))
96                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1255"))
97                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1256"))
98                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1257"))
99                  || (cs.name().equals("windows-1258"))
100                 || (cs.name().equals("windows-932"))
101                 || (cs.name().equals("x-mswin-936"))
102                 || (cs.name().equals("x-windows-949"))
103                 || (cs.name().equals("x-windows-950"))
104                 || (cs.name().equals("windows-31j"))
105                 || (cs.name().equals("JIS_X0201"))
106                 || (cs.name().equals("JIS_X0208-1990"))
107                 || (cs.name().equals("JIS_X0212"))
108                 || (cs.name().equals("Shift_JIS"))
109                 || (cs.name().equals("GB2312"))
110                 || (cs.name().equals("EUC-KR"))
111                 || (cs.name().equals("x-EUC-TW"))
112                 || (cs.name().equals("EUC-JP"))
113                 || (cs.name().equals("euc-jp-linux"))
114                 || (cs.name().equals("KOI8-R"))
115                 || (cs.name().equals("TIS-620"))
116                 || (cs.name().equals("x-ISCII91"))
117                 || (cs.name().equals("Big5"))
118                 || (cs.name().equals("Big5-HKSCS"))
119                 || (cs.name().equals("x-MS950-HKSCS"))
120                 || (cs.name().equals("ISO-2022-JP"))
121                 || (cs.name().equals("ISO-2022-KR"))
122                 || (cs.name().equals("x-ISO-2022-CN-CNS"))
123                 || (cs.name().equals("x-ISO-2022-CN-GB"))
124                 || (cs.name().equals("x-Johab"))
125                 || (cs instanceof GB18030));
126     }

12315     private static class Decoder extends CharsetDecoder {
12316 
12317         private static final char REPLACE_CHAR = '\uFFFD';
12318         private int currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12319 
12320         private Decoder(Charset cs) {
12321             super(cs, 1.0f, 2.0f);
12322         }
12323 
12324         private char getChar(int offset) {
12325             int byte1 = (offset >>8) & 0xFF;
12326             int byte2 = (offset & 0xFF);
12327             int start = 0, end = 0xFF;
12328 
12329             if (((byte1 < 0) || (byte1 > decoderIndex1.length))
12330                  || ((byte2 < start) || (byte2 > end))) {
12331                        return REPLACE_CHAR;
12332             }
12333 
12334             int n = (decoderIndex1[byte1] & 0xf) * (end - start + 1) + (byte2 - start);
12335             return decoderIndex2[decoderIndex1[byte1] >> 4].charAt(n);
12336         }
12337 
12338         protected char decodeDouble(int byte1, int byte2) {
12339             int start = 0x40, end = 0xFE;
12340             if (((byte1 < 0) || (byte1 > index1.length))
12341                 || ((byte2 < start) || (byte2 > end)))
12342                 return '\uFFFD';
12343 
12344             int n = (index1[byte1] & 0xf) * (end - start + 1) + (byte2 - start);
12345             return index2[index1[byte1] >> 4].charAt(n);
12346         }
12347 
12348         protected void implReset() {
12349             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12350         }
12351 
12352         private CoderResult decodeArrayLoop(ByteBuffer src,
12353                                             CharBuffer dst)
12354         {
12355             byte[] sa = src.array();
12356             int sp = src.arrayOffset() + src.position();
12357             int sl = src.arrayOffset() + src.limit();
12358             assert (sp <= sl);
12359             sp = (sp <= sl ? sp : sl);
12360 
12361             char[] da = dst.array();
12362             int dp = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.position();
12363             int dl = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.limit();
12364             assert (dp <= dl);
12365             dp = (dp <= dl ? dp : dl);
12366 
12367             int inputSize = 1;
12368 
12369             try {
12370                 while (sp < sl) {
12371                     int byte1 = 0 , byte2 = 0, byte3 = 0, byte4 = 0;
12372                     // Get the input byte
12373                     byte1 = sa[sp] & 0xFF;
12374                     inputSize = 1;
12375 
12376                     if ((byte1 & (byte)0x80) == 0){ // US-ASCII range
12377                         currentState = GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE;
12378                     }
12379                     else if (byte1 < 0x81 || byte1 > 0xfe) {
12380                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
12381                     }
12382                     else { // Either 2 or 4 byte sequence follows
12383                         if ( sl - sp < 2 )
12384                             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12385                         byte2 = sa[sp + 1] & 0xFF;
12386                         inputSize = 2;
12387 
12388                         if (byte2 < 0x30)
12389                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
12390                         else if (byte2 >= 0x30 && byte2 <= 0x39) {
12391                             currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12392 
12393                             if (sl - sp < 4)
12394                                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12395 
12396                             byte3 = sa[sp + 2] & 0xFF;
12397                             if (byte3 < 0x81 || byte3 > 0xfe)
12398                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(3);
12399 
12400                             byte4 = sa[sp + 3] & 0xFF;
12401                             inputSize = 4;
12402 
12403                             if (byte4 < 0x30 || byte4 > 0x39)
12404                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(4);
12405                         }
12406                         else if (byte2 == 0x7f || byte2 == 0xff ||
12407                                 (byte2 < 0x40 )) {
12408                            return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
12409                         }
12410                         else
12411                             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12412                     }
12413 
12414                     if (dl - dp < 1)
12415                         return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12416                     switch (currentState){
12417                         case GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE:
12418                             da[dp++] = (char)byte1;
12419                             break;
12420                         case GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE:
12421                             da[dp++] = decodeDouble(byte1, byte2);
12422                             break;
12423                         case GB18030_FOUR_BYTE:
12424                             int offset = (((byte1 - 0x81) * 10 +
12425                                            (byte2 - 0x30)) * 126 +
12426                                             byte3 - 0x81) * 10 + byte4 - 0x30;
12427                             int hiByte = (offset >>8) & 0xFF;
12428                             int lowByte = (offset & 0xFF);
12429 
12430                         // Mixture of table lookups and algorithmic calculation
12431                         // of character values.
12432 
12433                         // BMP Ranges
12434                         if (offset <= 0x4A62)
12435                             da[dp++] = getChar(offset);
12436                         else if (offset > 0x4A62 && offset <= 0x82BC)
12437                             da[dp++] = (char)(offset + 0x5543);
12438                         else if (offset >= 0x82BD && offset <= 0x830D)
12439                             da[dp++] = getChar(offset);
12440                         else if (offset >= 0x830D && offset <= 0x93A8)
12441                             da[dp++] = (char)(offset + 0x6557);
12442                         else if (offset >= 0x93A9 && offset <= 0x99FB)
12443                             da[dp++] = getChar(offset);
12444                         // Supplemental UCS planes handled via surrogates
12445                         else if (offset >= 0x2E248 && offset < 0x12E248) {
12446                             if (offset >= 0x12E248)
12447                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(4);
12448                             offset -= 0x1e248;
12449                             if ( dl - dp < 2)
12450                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12451                             // emit high + low surrogate
12452                             da[dp++] = (char)((offset - 0x10000) / 0x400 + 0xD800);
12453                             da[dp++] = (char)((offset - 0x10000) % 0x400 + 0xDC00);
12454                         }
12455                         else
12456                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(inputSize);
12457                         break;
12458                       }
12459                       sp += inputSize;
12460                 }
12461                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12462             } finally {
12463                 src.position(sp - src.arrayOffset());
12464                 dst.position(dp - dst.arrayOffset());
12465             }
12466         }
12467 
12468         private CoderResult decodeBufferLoop(ByteBuffer src,
12469                                             CharBuffer dst)
12470         {
12471             int mark = src.position();
12472 
12473             try {
12474                 while (src.hasRemaining()) {
12475                     int byte1 = 0, byte2 = 0, byte3 = 0, byte4 = 0;
12476                     byte1 = src.get() & 0xFF;
12477                     int inputSize = 1;
12478 
12479                     if ((byte1 & (byte)0x80) == 0){ // US-ASCII range
12480                         currentState = GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE;
12481                     }
12482                     else if (byte1 < 0x81 || byte1 > 0xfe) {
12483                         return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
12484                     }
12485                     else { // Either 2 or 4 byte sequence follows
12486                         if ( src.remaining() < 1 )
12487                             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12488                         byte2 = src.get() & 0xFF;
12489                         inputSize = 2;
12490 
12491                         if (byte2 < 0x30)
12492                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(1);
12493                         else if (byte2 >= 0x30 && byte2 <= 0x39) {
12494                             currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12495 
12496                             if (src.remaining() < 2)
12497                                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12498 
12499                             byte3 = src.get() & 0xFF;
12500                             if (byte3 < 0x81 || byte3 > 0xfe)
12501                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(3);
12502 
12503                             byte4 = src.get() & 0xFF;
12504                             inputSize = 4;
12505 
12506                             if (byte4 < 0x30 || byte4 > 0x39)
12507                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(4);
12508                         }
12509                         else if (byte2 == 0x7f || byte2 == 0xff ||
12510                                 (byte2 < 0x40 )) {
12511                            return CoderResult.malformedForLength(2);
12512                         }
12513                         else
12514                             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12515                     }
12516 
12517                     if (dst.remaining() < 1)
12518                         return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12519                     switch (currentState){
12520                         case GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE:
12521                             dst.put((char)byte1);
12522                             break;
12523                         case GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE:
12524                             dst.put(decodeDouble(byte1, byte2));
12525                             break;
12526                         case GB18030_FOUR_BYTE:
12527                             int offset = (((byte1 - 0x81) * 10 +
12528                                            (byte2 - 0x30)) * 126 +
12529                                             byte3 - 0x81) * 10 + byte4 - 0x30;
12530                             int hiByte = (offset >>8) & 0xFF;
12531                             int lowByte = (offset & 0xFF);
12532 
12533                         // Mixture of table lookups and algorithmic calculation
12534                         // of character values.
12535 
12536                         // BMP Ranges
12537                         if (offset <= 0x4A62)
12538                             dst.put(getChar(offset));
12539                         else if (offset > 0x4A62 && offset <= 0x82BC)
12540                             dst.put((char)(offset + 0x5543));
12541                         else if (offset >= 0x82BD && offset <= 0x830D)
12542                             dst.put(getChar(offset));
12543                         else if (offset >= 0x830D && offset <= 0x93A8)
12544                             dst.put((char)(offset + 0x6557));
12545                         else if (offset >= 0x93A9 && offset <= 0x99F9)
12546                             dst.put(getChar(offset));
12547                         // Supplemental UCS planes handled via surrogates
12548                         else if (offset >= 0x2E248 && offset < 0x12E248) {
12549                             if (offset >= 0x12E248)
12550                                 return CoderResult.malformedForLength(4);
12551                             offset -= 0x1e248;
12552                             if ( dst.remaining() < 2)
12553                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12554                             // emit high + low surrogate
12555                             dst.put((char)((offset - 0x10000) / 0x400 + 0xD800));
12556                             dst.put((char)((offset - 0x10000) % 0x400 + 0xDC00));
12557                         } else {
12558                             return CoderResult.malformedForLength(inputSize);
12559                         }
12560                     }
12561                     mark += inputSize;
12562                 }
12563                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12564             } finally {
12565                 src.position(mark);
12566             }
12567         }
12568 
12569 
12570         protected CoderResult decodeLoop(ByteBuffer src,
12571                                          CharBuffer dst)
12572         {
12573             if (src.hasArray() && dst.hasArray())
12574                 return decodeArrayLoop(src, dst);
12575             else
12576                 return decodeBufferLoop(src, dst);
12577         }
12578     }
12579 
12580     private static class Encoder extends CharsetEncoder {
12581 
12582         private int currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12583 
12584         private Encoder(Charset cs) {
12585             super(cs, 4.0f, 4.0f); // max of 4 bytes per char
12586         }
12587 
12588         public boolean canEncode(char c) {
12589             return ! Character.isSurrogate(c);
12590         }
12591 
12592         private final Surrogate.Parser sgp = new Surrogate.Parser();
12593 
12594         private int getGB18030(short[] outerIndex, String[] innerEncoderIndex,
12595                                char ch) {
12596             int offset = outerIndex[((ch & 0xff00) >> 8 )] << 8;
12597             return innerEncoderIndex[offset >> 12].charAt((offset & 0xfff) +
12598                         (ch & 0xff));
12599         }
12600 
12601         protected void implReset() {
12602             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12603         }
12604 
12605         private CoderResult encodeArrayLoop(CharBuffer src,
12606                                             ByteBuffer dst)
12607         {
12608             char[] sa = src.array();
12609             int sp = src.arrayOffset() + src.position();
12610             int sl = src.arrayOffset() + src.limit();
12611             assert (sp <= sl);
12612             sp = (sp <= sl ? sp : sl);
12613             byte[] da = dst.array();
12614             int dp = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.position();
12615             int dl = dst.arrayOffset() + dst.limit();
12616             assert (dp <= dl);
12617             dp = (dp <= dl ? dp : dl);
12618 
12619             int condensedKey = 0;  // expands to a four byte sequence
12620             int hiByte = 0, loByte = 0;
12621             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12622 
12623             try {
12624                 while (sp < sl) {
12625                     int inputSize = 1;
12626                     char c = sa[sp];
12627 
12628                     if (Character.isSurrogate(c)) {
12629                         if ((condensedKey=sgp.parse(c, sa, sp, sl)) < 0)
12630                             return sgp.error();
12631                         // Character.toCodePoint looks like
12632                         // (((high & 0x3ff) << 10) | (low & 0x3ff)) + 0x10000;
12633                         // so we add (0x2e248 - 0x10000) to get the "key".
12634                         condensedKey += 0x1E248;
12635                         currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12636                         inputSize = sgp.increment();
12637                     }
12638                     else if (c >= 0x0000 && c <= 0x007F) {
12639                         currentState = GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE;
12640                     }
12641                     else if (c <= 0xA4C6 || c >= 0xE000) {
12642                         int outByteVal = getGB18030(encoderIndex1,
12643                                                     encoderIndex2,
12644                                                     c);
12645                         if (outByteVal == 0xFFFD )
12646                                 return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
12647 
12648                         hiByte = (outByteVal & 0xFF00) >> 8;
12649                         loByte = (outByteVal & 0xFF);
12650 
12651                         condensedKey = (hiByte - 0x20) * 256 + loByte;
12652 
12653                         if (c >= 0xE000 && c < 0xF900)
12654                                 condensedKey += 0x82BD;
12655                         else if (c >= 0xF900)
12656                                 condensedKey += 0x93A9;
12657 
12658                         if (hiByte > 0x80)
12659                              currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12660                         else
12661                              currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12662                     }
12663                     else if (c >= 0xA4C7 && c <= 0xD7FF) {
12664                         condensedKey = c - 0x5543;
12665                         currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12666                     }
12667 
12668                     switch(currentState) {
12669                         case GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE:
12670                             if (dl - dp < 1)
12671                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12672                             da[dp++] = (byte)c;
12673                             break;
12674 
12675                         case GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE:
12676                             if (dl - dp < 2)
12677                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12678                             da[dp++] = (byte)hiByte;
12679                             da[dp++] = (byte)loByte;
12680                             break;
12681 
12682                         case GB18030_FOUR_BYTE: // Four Byte encoding
12683                             byte b1, b2, b3, b4;
12684 
12685                             if (dl - dp < 4)
12686                                 return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12687                             // Decompose the condensed key into its 4 byte equivalent
12688                             b4 = (byte)((condensedKey % 10) + 0x30);
12689                             condensedKey /= 10;
12690                             b3 = (byte)((condensedKey % 126) + 0x81);
12691                             condensedKey /= 126;
12692                             b2 = (byte)((condensedKey % 10) + 0x30);
12693                             b1 = (byte)((condensedKey / 10) + 0x81);
12694                             da[dp++] = b1;
12695                             da[dp++] = b2;
12696                             da[dp++] = b3;
12697                             da[dp++] = b4;
12698                             break;
12699                         default:
12700                             assert(false);
12701                         }
12702                     sp += inputSize;
12703                 }
12704             return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12705             } finally {
12706                 src.position(sp - src.arrayOffset());
12707                 dst.position(dp - dst.arrayOffset());
12708             }
12709         }
12710 
12711         private CoderResult encodeBufferLoop(CharBuffer src,
12712                                              ByteBuffer dst)
12713         {
12714             int condensedKey = 0;
12715             int hiByte = 0, loByte = 0;
12716             currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12717             int mark = src.position();
12718             try {
12719                 while (src.hasRemaining()) {
12720                     char c = src.get();
12721                     int inputSize = 1;
12722                     if (Character.isSurrogate(c)) {
12723                         if ((condensedKey = sgp.parse(c, src))<0)
12724                            return sgp.error();
12725                         condensedKey += 0x1e248;
12726                         currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12727                         inputSize = 2;
12728                     }
12729                     else if (c >= 0x0000 && c <= 0x007F) {
12730                         currentState = GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE;
12731                     }
12732                     else if (c <= 0xA4C6 || c >= 0xE000) {
12733                         int outByteVal = getGB18030(encoderIndex1,
12734                                                     encoderIndex2,
12735                                                     c);
12736                         if (outByteVal == 0xFFFD )
12737                             return CoderResult.unmappableForLength(1);
12738 
12739                         hiByte = (outByteVal & 0xFF00) >> 8;
12740                         loByte = (outByteVal & 0xFF);
12741 
12742                         condensedKey = (hiByte - 0x20) * 256 + loByte;
12743 
12744                         if (c >= 0xE000 && c < 0xF900)
12745                                 condensedKey += 0x82BD;
12746                         else if (c >= 0xF900)
12747                                 condensedKey += 0x93A9;
12748 
12749                         if (hiByte > 0x80)
12750                              currentState = GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE;
12751                         else
12752                              currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12753                     }
12754                     else if (c >= 0xA4C7 && c <= 0xD7FF) {
12755                         condensedKey = c - 0x5543;
12756                         currentState = GB18030_FOUR_BYTE;
12757                     }
12758 
12759                     if (currentState == GB18030_SINGLE_BYTE) {
12760                         if (dst.remaining() < 1)
12761                             return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12762                         dst.put((byte)c);
12763                     } else if (currentState == GB18030_DOUBLE_BYTE) {
12764                         if (dst.remaining() < 2)
12765                             return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12766                         dst.put((byte)hiByte);
12767                         dst.put((byte)loByte);
12768                     }
12769                     else { // Four Byte encoding
12770                         byte b1, b2, b3, b4;
12771 
12772                         if (dst.remaining() < 4)
12773                             return CoderResult.OVERFLOW;
12774                         // Decompose the condensed key into its 4 byte equivalent
12775                         b4 = (byte)((condensedKey % 10) + 0x30);
12776                         condensedKey /= 10;
12777                         b3 = (byte)((condensedKey % 126) + 0x81);
12778                         condensedKey /= 126;
12779                         b2 = (byte)((condensedKey % 10) + 0x30);
12780                         b1 = (byte)((condensedKey / 10) + 0x81);
12781                         dst.put(b1);
12782                         dst.put(b2);
12783                         dst.put(b3);
12784                         dst.put(b4);
12785                     }
12786                     mark += inputSize;
12787                 }
12788                 return CoderResult.UNDERFLOW;
12789             } finally {
12790                 src.position(mark);
12791             }
12792         }
12793         protected CoderResult encodeLoop(CharBuffer src,
12794                                          ByteBuffer dst)
12795         {
12796             if (src.hasArray() && dst.hasArray())
12797                 return encodeArrayLoop(src, dst);
12798             else
12799                 return encodeBufferLoop(src, dst);
12800         }
12801     }
12802 }
